item.title: How to make my compiler work (if it works u get admin on my server when its up)
item.dc:creator: @pkf0rl1f3 pkf0rl1f3
item.description:
@pkf0rl1f3 wrote:

@echo off
if exist “%programfiles%\Java” (call :compile “%programfiles%\Java”) else (goto error)
:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe")
if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java)
if defined p (goto end)
:error
echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
“%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe” http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
:end
echo Finished!
pause
exit

thts it

delete everything in your compiler and paste that into it
make sure you have java jdk and change the 03 to whatevr update your jdk is

btw what is your server ip? if the compiler says this:

Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API.
Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details.

That means it has compiled successfully.
[br][br][size=1]Posted on: August 11, 2008, 02:15:20 pm[/size][hr]java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp is the download site click on jdk 6 update 7 and check the box that says offline installation then click download on the java sun manager when it pops up let it download and instead of this in the code “C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_03\bin\javac.exe” -cp . *.java

put this instead of that one line:

“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_07\bin\javac.exe” -cp . *.java
